 temporal bone and the skull, and result in thickening of the ossicles. In tympanosclerosis, calcified plaques are typically diffuse in the middle ear cleft and involve the oval window.", "differential_diagnosis": "Differential diagnosis should include minor ossicular malformations presenting with a normal otoscopy, a conductive hearing loss, and abolished stapedial reflexes. In case of otosclerosis, an audiometry with stapedial reflex assessment should be recommended for the parents, siblings, and children (above 20 years of age) of the patient. In all the above etiologies, the progression of the hearing loss is generally slow.", "management_and_treatment": "The hearing loss due to stapes fixation is rarely profound and should always resolve early during follow-up. The conductive component of the hearing loss can be restored by surgery or hearing aids. The associated sensorineural component is managed by hearing aids or cochlear implants, depending on its severity. Sodium fluoride has been reported to slow the progression of otosclerosis lesions, and the consequent sensorineural hearing loss."}, {"name": "HOS", "sub_name": "Holt-Oram-Syndrom", "english": 0, "defenition": "Ein genetisches Syndrom mit Gliedma\u00dfenreduktionsdefekten, das durch Skelettanomalien der oberen Gliedma\u00dfen und leichte bis schwere angeborene Herzfehler gekennzeichnet ist.", "synonyms": "Dysplasie, atriodigitale, Typ 1, HOS, Herz-Hand-Syndrom Typ 1, ", "prevalence": "Unbekannt", "inheritance": "Autosomal-dominant\u00a0", "age_of_onset": "Neugeborenenzeit", "ICD-10": "Q87.2", "OMIM": "142900", "UMLS": "C0265264", "MeSH": "C535326", "GARD": "6666", "MedDRA": "10050469", "epidemiology": "Die Krankheit wurde weltweit beschrieben, in Ungarn wurde ihre Pr\u00e4valenz unter Lebendgeburten zu 1/ 100,000 bestimmt.", "clinical_description": "selbst, sondern um Ph\u00e4nokopie-Syndrome (siehe die Differentialdiagnosen weiter unten). Zu den Anomalien des Radialstrahls der oberen Gliedma\u00dfen geh