": "Inherited FII deficiency is caused by mutations in the F2 gene (11p11-q12) encoding prothrombin.", "diagnostic_methods": "Diagnosis is based on prolonged prothrombin and activated partial thromboplastin times (PT, aPTT) and on low FII coagulant activity measured using a PT based assay. Molecular testing is available, but is unnecessary for diagnosis.", "differential_diagnosis": "Differential diagnoses include deficiencies of factors V, VII, X, VIII, IX, XI, XIII or acquired deficiencies in FII (lupus anticoagulant).", "antenatal_diagnosis": "Prenatal diagnosis is available for the most severe forms.", "genetic_counseling": "Transmission is autosomal recessive. Genetic counseling should be offered to at-risk couples (both individuals are carriers of a disease-causing mutation) informing them of the 25% risk of having an affected child at each pregnancy.", "management_and_treatment": "Prothrombin Complex Concentrates (PCCs) or fresh frozen plasma (if PCCs are not available) are usually used to treat hemorrhagic episodes.", "prognosis": "Prognosis is good with early diagnosis and adequate treatment."}, {"name": "Hypoprothrombin\u00e4mie, erworbene", "sub_name": "Faktor II-Mangel, erworbener", "english": 0, "defenition": "Unsere Website hostet keinerlei Werbung\nUnsere Partnerschaften beeinflussen in keiner Weise unsere Ver\u00f6ffentlichungspolitik\n", "synonyms": "Hypoprothrombin\u00e4mie, erworbene, Prothrombin-Mangel, erworbener, ", "ICD-10": "D68.4", "UMLS": "C0392610", "GARD": "475", "summary": "Eine Kurzbeschreibung der Krankheit wird derzeit erstellt. Weiterf\u00fchrende Informationen zu dieser Krankheit k\u00f6nnen \u00fcber das Menu  am unteren Bildrand abgerufen werden."}, {"name": "Hyposmie-nasale und okul\u00e4re Hypoplasie-hypogonadotroper Hypogonadismus-Syndrom", "english": 0, "defenition": "Zusatzinformationen\n", "synonyms": "Arhinie-Mikrophthalmie-Syndrom Bosma, Bosma-Henkin-Christiansen-Syndrom, ", "prevalence": "<1 / 1 000 000", "inheritance": "U